ifest verify arm (PinnedAgentPubkeys path mirrors CompleteSetMint). assert_complete_set_balanced + assert_total_ctf_conserved + assert_no_post_init_mint all called in accept arm. Predecessor hash 4845265803 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-18R Phase 2 (2026-05-06; preflight `handover/directives/2026-05-06_TB18R_PHASE_2_REMEDIATION_DIRECTIVE.md` §3.2): added `AttemptOutcome::PartialAccepted` arm to `refine_rejection_class_via_attempt_telemetry` rejection-arm match. Mirrors the existing LeanPass-misuse arm (panic-in-debug, fall-back-to-PredicateFailed-in-release) since step_partial_ok stays CAS-only per R3 §1.3 amended and PartialAccepted reaching the rejection arm would be an invariant violation. Predecessor hash 88e93d93 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-18R R3.fix (2026-05-06; preflight handover/ai-direct/TB-18R_R3FIX_STEP_B_cas_reload.md §2.1 + §3.2): refine_rejection_class_via_attempt_telemetry now retries on initial CidNotFound — promotes read lock to write lock, calls cas_w.reload_index_from_sidecar(), drops, retries read once. On second miss falls back to base_class (legacy ProposalTelemetry CID + truly-absent CID both still graceful). Closes L0-smoke-2026-05-06 split-brain: sequencer.cas in-memory index was stale wrt evaluator's separate handle writes; refine helper missed AttemptTelemetry and fell back to PredicateFailed instead of mapping outcome→fine class. Class 4 surface; STEP_B parallel-branch worktree `tb-18r-r3fix-cas-reload`. Pure-additive on the read path; no behavior change for legitimate reads or fallback paths. Predecessor TB-18R R3 hash 423764d8 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-18R R3 (2026-05-06; preflight handover/ai-direct/TB-18R_R3_STEP_B_admission.md §1.2 + §3.1 Design D): added pub free function `refine_rejection_class_via_attempt_telemetry(cas, tx, base_class)` (preflight §1.2) + extended `record_rejection` to invoke it on the `predicate_passes=false` rejection arm so runtime-path WorkTx (R2-shipped failure paths) routes to L4.E with refined RejectionClass ∈ {LeanFailed=6, ParseFailed=7, SorryBlocked=8, LlmError=9} via AttemptTelemetry CAS read. Pure-additive: legacy proposal_cid → ProposalTelemetry → fall-back to base PredicateFailed (preserves TB-7 audit chain). LeanPass-on-rejection-arm panics in debug + warn-and-fallback in release (preflight §3.6). Aborted falls back (R4 TerminalAbortRecord territory). Class 4 surface per `feedback_class4_cannot_hide_in_class3`; STEP_B parallel-branch worktree `tb-18r-r3-admission`. No other admission logic touched; legacy chains replay byte-identical. Predecessor TB-15 R3 closure hash 0453e735 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-15 R3 closure (2026-05-04; Codex R2 VETO TB15-CAS-ID closure): TaskBankruptcyTx Step 3.5 dispatch arm + apply_one Stage 3.5 updated to consume new BankruptcyAutopsyDerivation struct returned by derive_autopsies_for_bankruptcy (was Vec<(AgentAutopsyCapsule, Vec<u8>)>; now Vec<BankruptcyAutopsyDerivation> with .capsule + .private_bytes + .stored_capsule_bytes fields). Dispatch arm reads d.capsule.capsule_id; apply_one writes d.stored_capsule_bytes (the bytes whose sha256 == capsule_id, ensuring cas.get(&capsule_id) is resolvable). Predecessor R2 hash f4119a41 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-15 R2 closure (2026-05-04; Gemini R1 VETO Q12 — replay-determinism activation gate): TaskBankruptcyTx dispatch arm Step 3.5 + apply_one Stage 3.5 BOTH wrapped in `if crate::runtime::autopsy_capsule::is_autopsy_active_at(bk.timestamp_logical)` gate. Default `TB15_AUTOPSY_ACTIVATION_LOGICAL_T = 0` keeps fresh chains always-active (every new chain starts at logical_t=1 ≥ 0); pre-TB-15 chain migration would override the constant to skip pre-cutoff TaskBankruptcyTx rows per `feedback_no_retroactive_evidence_rewrite` going-forward only. Verification baseline 2026-05-04: ZERO production chains contain TaskBankruptcyTx (grep `git log refs/transitions/main` across 10 evidence runtime_repo dirs). Predecessor TB-15 Atom 3 hash 9fa59362 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-15 Atom 3 (202