-"src/economy/monetary_invariant.rs" = "d41c91cb0ad8204bf7a50c86a96ec473e3cbb4119b3ea189a7df048530334f0a"  # rehashed by Stage C P-M6 / Phase F.5 (2026-05-09 session #32): added TypedTx::BuyWithCoinRouter to assert_no_post_init_mint allow-list (router is symmetric Coin→collateral movement: balances_t -1 payC + conditional_collateral_t +1 payC; total_supply_micro 6-holding sum preserved bit-exact; YES/NO + pool reserves NOT Coin per architect §7.5 rule 2). Predecessor hash 26c7d532ef38de07e22f8482dde0e0c80fc60950a5222cd362a4cd0277f56820 superseded.  # rehashed by Stage C P-M5 / Phase F.4 (2026-05-09 session #32): added TypedTx::CpmmSwap to assert_no_post_init_mint allow-list (swap is pure share rotation between trader and pool reserves; balances_t / conditional_collateral_t / lp_share_balances_t UNCHANGED; total_supply_micro 6-holding sum preserved bit-exact). Predecessor hash 404a24e7d44fd535301de84da4c1c255aba93cd830d127bd9e449cb58f988419 superseded.  # rehashed by Stage C P-M4 / Phase F.3 (2026-05-09 session #31): two changes — (a) added TypedTx::CpmmPool to assert_no_post_init_mint allow-list (pool creation moves YES + NO from provider's conditional_share_balances_t into pool reserves + credits LP shares; pool reserves NOT Coin per architect §7.5 rule 2; LP shares NOT Coin per rule 3; total_supply_micro UNCHANGED); (b) extended assert_complete_set_balanced sum_yes / sum_no totals to also count `cpmm_pools_t[event_id].pool_yes / pool_no` — pool reserves are claims against the SAME locked collateral, so the symmetric-branch strict-equality `sum_yes == sum_no == collateral` MUST count pool reserves alongside individual conditional_share_balances_t totals (otherwise valid post-CpmmPoolTx state where YES/NO have moved from provider individual balance to pool reserves would falsely trip MonetaryInvariantViolation). The CTF-MIN-SAFE asymmetric branch is unchanged. Predecessor hash c1f6bd0e91 superseded.  # rehashed by Stage C P-M2 / Phase F.1 (2026-05-09 session #29): added TypedTx::CompleteSetMerge to assert_no_post_init_mint allow-list (merge is balance ↔ collateral migration only, never mints; CTF conservation enforced at dispatch site via assert_total_ctf_conserved + assert_complete_set_balanced). Predecessor hash c4e1e25840 superseded.  # rehashed by Stage C VETO remediation Phase E.3 (2026-05-09 session #28): split `assert_complete_set_balanced` into symmetric branch (strict `sum_yes == sum_no == coll`) and asymmetric branch (post-resolution partial-redemption; `min()` audit-marked CTF-MIN-SAFE) per Codex 2026-05-09 G2 audit defect 1 + plan cached-noodle.md §C.E.3. Functionally equivalent to the pre-split min() logic (TB-13 + TB-14 + TB-16 R1 tests preserve), but makes the two regimes explicit + enforceable by `tests/constitution_economy_strict_equality.rs`. Predecessor TB-16 Atom 7 R1 hash 91f66421 superseded.
