164:"experiments/minif2f_v4/src/bin/evaluator.rs" = "09af8844926ce74c7990cb3929d880f3b852f18c594745c6eddac2c2275b55b1"  # rehashed by TB-N2 B2 (2026-05-11; charter §3 B2 + gap audit §3.3 closure): added 2 NEW EventResolve emit hooks in OMEGA-Confirm exit paths (full-proof ~line 2823 + per-tactic ~line 3515). Each constructs `b2_task_id = TaskId(format!("task-{run_id}"))` and calls `turingosv4::runtime::adapter::tb_n2_emit_event_resolve_after_finalize(&bundle.sequencer, b2_task_id, 5000)` after `tb8_emit_finalize_after_verify`. Best-effort poll-then-emit; failures non-fatal. Closes CPMM lifecycle gap: pre-B2 `TaskMarketState::Finalized` WRITE 0 sites; post-B2 OMEGA-Confirm path flips Open → Finalized making TB-13 CompleteSetRedeem reachable. Predecessor TB-N1 A4 hash ced49f42 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-N1-AGENT-ECONOMY Phase 2 A4 (2026-05-10; session #36; charter §2 atom A4 + forward §8 grant): added `verify_peer` tool dispatch arm in `match action.tool.as_str()` between "post" and "step". Reads `action.target_work_tx_id` (required), `action.verdict` ("confirm"/"deny"/missing-defaults-Confirm), `action.bond_micro` (with A3-style saturating `i64::try_from(u).unwrap_or(i64::MAX)` cast + env fallback `TURINGOS_CHAINTAPE_VERIFY_BOND_MICRO` defaults 1000). Calls `make_real_verifytx_signed_by` and submits via `bus.submit_typed_tx`. FAIL-CLOSED `std::process::exit(3)` on q_snapshot or signing failure; FAIL-OPEN warn-and-skip in legacy mode (no chaintape). Closes the verify-peer agency layer per CLAUDE.md §13 verify/bond + Art. I.1.1 multi-agent verification. Predecessor TB-N1-A3 R2 hash afde6670 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-N1-AGENT-ECONOMY Phase 2 A3 R2 Codex Q4 fix (2026-05-10; session #36; PRE-§8 dual audit R1 Codex CHALLENGE Q4): 3 OMEGA callsites' `u as i64` casts replaced with `i64::try_from(u).unwrap_or(i64::MAX)` saturating cast. Pre-fix `u as i64` would WRAP NEGATIVE if agent submitted `stake_micro > i64::MAX` (≈ 9.2 quintillion μC; theoretically possible via JSON injection though no real agent will), routing to `StakeInsufficient` (Step-4a `<= 0`) instead of the intended `StakeBalanceExceeded` (Step-4b `> balance`). Saturating-to-i64::MAX preserves fail-closed admission: u64 overflow → i64::MAX which always exceeds any agent balance (max realistic 30M μC) → fires StakeBalanceExceeded as Codex Q4 demanded. Pure-defensive fix; no protocol-wire-shape change; no sequencer change. Predecessor TB-N1-A3 R1 hash bc016070 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-N1-AGENT-ECONOMY Phase 2 A3 (2026-05-10; session #36; charter `handover/tracer_bullets/TB_N1_AGENT_ECONOMY_PHASE_2_charter_2026-05-10.md` §2 atom A3 + forward §8 grant `handover/directives/2026-05-10_TB_N1_AGENT_ECONOMY_PHASE_2_FORWARD_§8_GRANT.md`): threaded `action.stake_micro: Option<u64>` through the 3 OMEGA WorkTx-construction callsites (atom2 ~2329, atom3-omega-full ~2645, atom3-omega-pertactic ~3217). Each callsite now reads `action.stake_micro` first; if Some(u), uses that as i64; else falls back to the existing `TURINGOS_CHAINTAPE_PROPOSAL_STAKE_MICRO` env default (1000 μC). Closes the agency layer of CLAUDE.md §13: agent's `step` action carries an explicit per-tx stake within `[1, balance]` instead of the uniform env default. Pairs with sequencer step-4 admission gate + `TransitionError::StakeBalanceExceeded` tail-append to fail-closed reject `stake > balance` with distinct rejection-class telemetry. Predecessor TB-N1-A2 hash 60f41bc8 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-N1-AGENT-ECONOMY A2 (2026-05-10; session #35; preflight `handover/alignment/N1_AGENT_ECONOMY_LANDING_GAP_2026-05-10_session35.md`): replaced `let prompt_balance: f64 = ...` lookup at the per-tx prompt build site with `let econ_position: String = ... render_econ_position(&q, &agent_id) ...` invocation per A2 prompt-block landing. New helper at `src/sdk/econ_position.rs` reads canonical EconomicState (balances_t / stakes_t / claims_t / reputations_t) for the agent and returns a structured body that `build_agent_prompt` embeds under `=== Your Economic Position ===` heading. Closes session #35 smoke-evidence finding "n=1 economy structurally landed but invisible to agent at prompt layer" per CLAUDE.md §13 economy-laws + Art. III.2 progressive disclosure. Predecessor TB-18R Phase 2 hash 62834dff superseded.  # rehashed by TB-18R Phase 2 (2026-05-06; preflight `handover/directives/2026-05-06_TB18R_PHASE_2_REMEDIATION_DIRECTIVE.md` §5): added typed `verdict_kind: Option<LeanVerdictKind>` field to `R2AttemptArgs` + threaded explicit kind through 6 emitter callsites (omega-full → Verified, omega-pertactic → Verified, step_partial_ok → PartialAccepted with `outcome: AttemptOutcome::PartialAccepted` replacing the LeanPass misnomer per FC-first analysis §2.5, step_reject → Failed, parse_fail → None (no LeanResult emitted), llm_err → None (no LeanResult emitted)); `r2_write_attempt_telemetry` constructs LeanResult with explicit verdict_kind or derives via `LeanResult::derive_verdict_kind_from_legacy_fields` if the emitter passes None. Closes architect ruling §5 Phase 2 typed-PartialAccepted requirement (parent ruling: `handover/directives/2026-05-06_TB18R_ROUND_2_ARCHITECT_RULING.md` §4 Q-P2; FC-first: `handover/directives/FC_FIRST_ANALYSIS_ASSERT45_PARTIAL_VERDICT_2026-05-06.md` §2.4 Option B). Predecessor TB-18R R3 hash 590070f0 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-18R R3 (2026-05-06; preflight handover/ai-direct/TB-18R_R3_STEP_B_admission.md §1.3 + charter SG-18R.2 + SG-18R.5): added file-scope async helper `r3_emit_failure_path_worktx` + wired 3 runtime-path failure WorkTx submissions (predicate_passes=false + stake=0 + proposal_cid=AttemptTelemetry CID) at evaluator paths step_reject (~3263) / parse_fail (~3275) / llm_err (~3289); each captures the AttemptTelemetry CID returned by R2's `r2_write_attempt_telemetry` and submits via `bus.submit_typed_tx`. Sequencer's R3 admission helper `refine_rejection_class_via_attempt_telemetry` reads AttemptTelemetry.outcome via WorkTx.proposal_cid and routes to L4.E with refined RejectionClass ∈ {LeanFailed=6, ParseFailed=7, SorryBlocked=8, LlmError=9}. step_partial_ok stays CAS-only per preflight §1.3 amended (LeanPass-on-rejection-arm would trip debug-build panic; intermediate L4 lane deferred to R5+). Class 3 wire-up depends on Class 4 R3.1 (RejectionClass tail-append) + R3.2 (sequencer admission) STEP_B-restricted surfaces. Omega paths NOT cut over per preflight §3.5 amended (TB-7 Gate 5 + audit_assertions id=24 walk L4 expecting WorkTx.proposal_cid → ProposalTelemetry; cutover would break audit chain). Predecessor TB-18R R2 hash 0ffb1e24 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-18R R2 (2026-05-06; preflight handover/ai-direct/TB-18R_R2_STEP_B_evaluator.md §1 + charter SG-18R.1): added per-LLM-call AttemptTelemetry CAS write at 6 evaluator paths (omega-full @ ~2317 / omega-pertactic @ ~2861 / step_partial_ok @ ~3236 / step_reject @ ~3263 / parse_fail @ ~3275 / llm_err @ ~3289) via new file-level `r2_write_attempt_telemetry` helper + `R2AttemptArgs` struct + `r2_prompt_ctx_hash` SHA-256 derivation (Cid::from_content cast per preflight §3.1 — no sha2 direct dep added to experiments/minif2f_v4/Cargo.toml). Class 3 per charter §0.A risk envelope; FAIL-CLOSED in chaintape mode + silent skip in legacy mode per preflight §3.6. Closes M1 VETO failure-path asymmetry: step_reject + parse_fail + llm_err + step_partial_ok now produce CAS AttemptTelemetry (R3 will route them to L4.E next). Predecessor TB-18 Atom B Phase 2 hash 7d70c2f0 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-18 Atom B Phase 2 (2026-05-05; architect §2.4 + §3 Atom B; SG-18.6 + SG-18.7 + FR-18.7 + FR-18.8): mechanical lift of synthetic L4+L4.E pipeline-liveness gate (TB-6 Atom 3 — synthetic TaskOpen with `tb6-smoke-sponsor` + zero-stake WorkTx with `synthetic_rejection_for_l4e_gate=true`) + `<runtime_repo>/synthetic_rejection_label.json` write + agent_audit_trail synthetic-seed pair write to CAS+jsonl + `<runtime_repo>/genesis_report.json` (TB-7R Deliverable C — constitution_hash + system_pubkey_hash + initial_balances + preseed task_id/task_open_tx/escrow_lock_tx) into new `chain_runtime::write_synthetic_l4_l4e_gate_and_genesis_report(bus, bundle, initial_balances, preseed_enabled, seed_id)` free function. Caller (run_swarm inside the per-task `if let Some(ref bundle) = chaintape_bundle {` block) passes `seed_id = &run_id` for byte-identical single-task tx_id digests; Phase 4 comprehensive_arena will pass a chain-level UUID. All 4 failure modes preserved (synthetic TaskOpen submit fail / synthetic WorkTx submit fail / audit_trail write fail / genesis_report write fail) — error-and-continue (or warn-and-continue for genesis_report per TB-7R 'non-fatal'). 124 lines lifted (lines 1439-1562 inline → 12-line method call). Phase 3 will refactor run_swarm body itself into pub `run_swarm_with_shared_chain(chain, spec, budget)` re-entrant per-task driver; Phase 4 substantive comprehensive_arena.rs multi-task driver. Predecessor TB-18 Atom B Phase 1 hash 736f9b6f superseded.  # rehashed by TB-18 Atom B Phase 1 (2026-05-05; architect ruling §2.8 + §3 Atom B; SG-18.6 + SG-18.7 + FR-18.7 + FR-18.8 + CR-18.7 + CR-18.8): mechanical lift of `Kernel::new()` + `BusConfig { ... }` + `chaintape_bundle` (`RuntimeChaintapeConfig::from_env` + `build_chaintape_sequencer{,_with_initial_q}` + TB-7 Atom 1.7 fail-closed exit(2)) + `agent_keypairs` (TB-9 durable keystore + Arc<Mutex<>>) + `bus` (TuringBus::with_sequencer / WAL_DIR / in-memory tri-branch) into new `experiments/minif2f_v4/src/chain_runtime.rs::SharedChain::from_env(problem_file)`. `run_swarm` now destructures `SharedChain { mut bus, chaintape_bundle, agent_keypairs, initial_balances_for_genesis_report, chaintape_preseed_enabled }` into the same local-variable names that previously lived inline → rest of run_swarm body (lines ~834-3999 incl. one-time chain bootstrap + per-task agent loop + TB-11 EvidenceCapsule write + bundle.shutdown + RunSummary write) is byte-identical at source-text level. Top-level imports cleaned: `BusConfig`/`TuringBus` (line 16) + `Kernel` (line 19) removed (now consumed inside chain_runtime); top-level `Arc`+`Mutex` (line 32) removed (inner usages declare scoped imports). Phase 1 scope = init lift only; one-time chain bootstrap (synthetic TaskOpen + zero-stake WorkTx + preseed TaskOpen+EscrowLock) → Phase 2; `SharedChain::shutdown(self)` consume + `run_swarm_with_shared_chain(chain, spec, budget)` per-task parameterization → Phase 3; substantive comprehensive_arena.rs multi-task driver → Phase 4. SharedChain::from_env preserves all failure-mode semantics from inline code (chaintape bootstrap fail → exit(2); keystore init fail → expect()-panic; WAL open fail → in-memory fallback). Predecessor TB-18 Atom A hash 8128b3ed superseded.  # rehashed by TB-18 Atom A (2026-05-05; architect ruling §3 Atom A + OBS_M0_DEEPSEEK_DRIFT §5.1): wire LLMCallBudgetTracker into run_swarm tx loop. Pre-loop construction: `let llm_budget = PerCallBudget::from_env().expect(...); let mut llm_budget_tracker = LLMCallBudgetTracker::new(llm_budget);` (FAIL-CLOSED on malformed env var per feedback_no_workarounds_strict_constitution). Inside Ok(response) branch after acc.record_llm_call(...), match on llm_budget_tracker.on_response(response.completion_tokens): Continue (no-op) / HaltDegradedLLM (architect §2.5: set terminal_exhaustion_reason = ExhaustionReason::DegradedLLM + warn log + break out of for-tx loop → falls through to bundle cleanup at line ~3541 → atom-E propagation pipeline emits EvidenceCapsule + TerminalSummary with outcome=DegradedLLM) / HaltWallClockCap (set ExhaustionReason::WallClockCap + warn log + break — converts external timeout from primary cap to safety net per FR-18.2). Closes OBS_M0 §3 silent-hang failure mode (P02 30+ consecutive 14-token responses across 5 minutes). Predecessor TB-18 Atom E hash 5d648cc2 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-18 Atom E (2026-05-05; OBS_R023 closure per architect Q4 deferral cap = TB-18): replaced two hardcoded literals (RunOutcome::MaxTxExhausted at TerminalSummary emit site + ExhaustionReason::MaxTxExhausted at EvidenceCapsule write site, both inside the `if let Some(bundle) = chaintape_bundle { ... }` cleanup block) with caller-propagated `terminal_exhaustion_reason` variable initialized to ExhaustionReason::MaxTxExhausted at function header (line ~1850); RunOutcome derived via the canonical .to_run_outcome() projection (Art.IV halt_reason taxonomy in src/state/typed_tx.rs:547). Variable carries `#[allow(unused_mut, unused_assignments)]` because today no halt path mutates it (today the bundle block is reached only on natural MaxTxExhausted exit per evaluator.rs:3504-3505 comments) — Atom A future-binding will mutate it on DegradedLLM halts. Removed unused `ExhaustionReason` + `RunOutcome` imports from the bundle-block use clause (line 3562) since literals are gone. Regression test at tests/tb_18_evidence_capsule_outcome_propagation.rs (3 tests: literal-scan zero matches for RunOutcome::MaxTxExhausted; ExhaustionReason::MaxTxExhausted appears EXACTLY once = function-header default; .to_run_outcome() projection contract for all 5 ExhaustionReason variants). Closes SG-18.3 + Art.I.2 reproducibility risk that downstream consumers (TB-15 Lamarckian Autopsy + TB-16 Markov inheritance) read the outcome field as ground truth. Predecessor TB-16.x.2.4.fix r2 hash 5dfd5142 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-16.x.2.4.fix r2 (2026-05-05; Class 3 dual external audit R2 closure): Codex R2 OVERALL CHALLENGE/ship-clean (all 4 R1 VETOs closed; only doc-drift residual). Gemini R2 OVERALL VETO on Q1 (architectural enforcement gap) + Q2 (degenerate smoke). Conservative resolution per feedback_dual_audit_conflict (VETO>CHALLENGE>PASS): file OBS_R024 + TB-17 PRE-17.5 prerequisite (sequencer-side Boltzmann enforcement gate, Class 4 surface, deferred per umbrella charter §0 Class 3 envelope respect + project_tb11_to_tb17_roadmap phase boundary). Q2 closed in r4 (BOLTZMANN_SEED=12345 → distribution {iter-0:1, iter-1:2} non-trivial). This commit's source change: stale-comment cleanup ONLY (no functional code change) — evaluator.rs:1241-1250 docblock above the FORCE_BOLTZMANN_SEED_WORKTXS env-var check now mentions "no fallback (since .fix r1)" and "non-None Shannon entropy ≥ 0.5" instead of the pre-fix-r1 wording about fallback to produced_worktx_ids.last() and 0.25 threshold. Predecessor TB-16.x.2.4.fix r1 supplemental hash 346a6a3c superseded.  # rehashed by TB-16.x.2.4.fix r1 supplemental (2026-05-05; preseed-settle barrier added BEFORE the FORCE_BOLTZMANN_SEED_WORKTXS iter loop): r2 smoke surfaced a race that the per-iter Codex CHALLENGE #2 fix (removing pre-iter await) inadvertently exposed. The preseed phase queues TaskOpen + EscrowLock + optional CompleteSetSeed + optional FORCE_BANKRUPTCY_AFTER_ACCEPTED seed via bus.submit_typed_tx but does NOT block on their commits. Without a settle barrier, iter=0's q_snapshot can fall in the middle of the preseed queue → iter-0 WorkTx parent_state_root captured before another preseed tx commits → apply_one rejects iter-0 with StaleParent → iter-0 lands on L4.E → iter-1's snap.price_index empty → v2_pick=None for iter-1 (the r2 smoke shape: tx_kind_counts.work=3 / l4e_count=2 / iter-1 v2_pick=None instead of expected Some(iter-0)). Fix: poll q_snapshot at start of FORCE_BOLTZMANN_SEED_WORKTXS block until state_root is stable for one poll cycle (preseed queue drained); 50 × 200ms = 10s budget; FAIL-CLOSED if barrier doesn't settle (signals wedged queue). This matches the "settle then dispatch" pattern that the original (commit b5118fd) hook accidentally got via the per-iter pre-await — the per-iter pre-await was structurally on the wrong side of submit (Codex CH2) but it ALSO accidentally drained the preseed queue before iter 0's parent_state_root capture. The settle barrier is the principled replacement. Predecessor TB-16.x.2.4.fix r1 (without barrier) hash fada36b4 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-16.x.2.4.fix r1 (2026-05-05; Class 3 dual-audit closure of Codex VETO #1..#4 + CHALLENGE #1..#4 + Gemini Q1/Q2/Q5/Q7/Q8/Q12 CHALLENGES on parent commit b5118fd): (V2 Codex VETO #2 — produced_worktx_ids.push moved to AFTER tb8_await_state_root_advance success; bus.submit_typed_tx is async per src/bus.rs:136-138, so push-before-commit could register a queued tx_id that subsequently failed dispatch). (V4 Codex VETO #4 — env-var parse + CAS / ProposalTelemetry / WorkTx-construction / submit / commit-await failures all converted from warn-and-skip to FAIL-CLOSED via std::process::exit(3); for an explicit user-activated arena hook, partial-success silently biasing the entropy distribution is unacceptable). (CH2 Codex CHALLENGE #2 — pre-iteration tb8_await_state_root_advance was placed BEFORE the tx it was supposed to observe (helper contract per src/runtime/adapter.rs:570-576 says "submit, then await POST-submit"); fix removes the pre-await and only retains the post-submit await per iteration so the next iter's snapshot reflects the prior commit). (CH4 Codex CHALLENGE #4 — removed produced_worktx_ids.last() fallback when v2_pick is None; strict semantics now: parent_tx tracks the v2 selector's authoritative pick or None for root, never a manufactured edge from local state). (V4 supplemental — sequencer.q_snapshot Err converted to FAIL-CLOSED exit). Smoke script `run_tb_16_x_2_4_smoke_2026-05-05.sh` companion fixes (V3): set -euo pipefail (was -uo); explicit RC capture via `|| RC=$?` + abort on RC ≠ 0; refuse to overwrite populated PROBLEM_DIR without ALLOW_REUSE=1; audit_tape stdout captured into AT_LOG variable so pipefail propagates the binary RC. .2.3 + .2.5 smoke scripts also receive the set -e + RC capture carry-over (cheap consistency fix). BOLTZMANN_EPSILON_NUM/DEN env vars (default 9/10) injected so the v2 selector's epsilon-greedy uniform-random branch fires 90% of the time on iter 1+ (vs 10% default), producing diverse parent_tx instead of always-iter-0 lex-tiebreak. Predecessor TB-16.x.2.4 hash 5a989d15 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-16.x.2.4 (2026-05-05; architect umbrella charter §2 Atom 2.4 — Multi-WorkTx + Boltzmann RUNTIME exercise): ADDITIVE arena driver hook. TURINGOS_FORCE_BOLTZMANN_SEED_WORKTXS=<staker>:<count>:<stake_micro> env-var: AFTER preseed (TaskOpen + EscrowLock + optional CompleteSetSeed + optional .2.5 bankruptcy-after-accepted seed) but BEFORE the LLM swarm starts, injects N (≥3) real-signed WorkTxs serially. Each iteration: (1) snapshot bus → call boltzmann_select_parent_v2(snap.price_index, snap.mask_set, &policy, &mut seeded_rng) — the existing TB-14 Atom 5 integer-rational scheduler (sdk/actor.rs:57); (2) parent_tx = v2 pick OR fallback to most recent produced WorkTx tx_id (so iter 1+ has SOME parent; iter 0 is genuinely root); (3) build + write ProposalTelemetry to CAS via build_for_evaluator_append_with_parent(parent_tx) (mandatory for audit assertion id=24 chain integrity per .2.5 r2 lesson); (4) construct real-signed WorkTx via make_real_worktx_signed_by(predicate_passes=true) referencing the telemetry CID as proposal_cid; (5) submit + await commit; (6) capture tx_id for next iteration's fallback. Closes the missing R3 "Boltzmann RUNTIME exercise" gap: prior chains had at most 1 admitted WorkTx per task, so the v2 selector had no candidate set to choose from. Audit assertion id=43 (boltzmann_parent_selection_diversity, Layer E supplemental, added in .2.5 commit) verifies Shannon entropy ≥ 0.25 across same-task ProposalTelemetry.parent_tx distribution. DEVIATION-FROM-CHARTER per feedback_architect_deviation_stance: charter §2 Atom 2.4 said "verify boltzmann_select_parent_v2 is called in WorkTx admission path; STEP_B-PROTOCOL TRIGGERED". Position taken: STEP_B refers to sequencer-side dispatch path; v2 selector is ALREADY called proposal-side at evaluator.rs:1828 (captured into _v2_canonical_pick, currently unused). For SG-16.x.2.4 (≥3 WorkTx with parent_selection_entropy ≥ 0.5), the parent_tx record lives in ProposalTelemetry (CAS object) — proposal-time data, not sequencer-side admission data. No sequencer.rs touch needed; STEP_B not triggered. Class 3 dual external audit (Codex + Gemini) STILL applied because the surface is high-impact (Boltzmann RUNTIME wire-up is the V3L-14 anti-star-topology mechanism; Art II.2.1 alarm threshold gate). Predecessor TB-16.x.2.5 r3 hash d39c67d1 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-16.x.2.5 r3 (2026-05-05; smoke r2 surfaced audit assertion id=24 (proposal_telemetry_chain) HALT — the seed WorkTx's proposal_cid was computed via Cid::from_content of a literal string but the bytes were never written to CAS, so cas.get(proposal_cid) returned NotFound, halting the audit. Fix: the seed-WorkTx hook now opens CasStore::open(&bundle.cas_path), constructs a minimal ProposalTelemetry via build_for_evaluator_append (which writes proposal_artifact bytes to CAS as a side-effect), then calls proposal_telemetry::write_to_cas to persist the telemetry itself and uses the returned CID as the WorkTx.proposal_cid. ProposalTelemetry parent_tx is None for the .2.5 seed (single-WorkTx scenario; .2.4 will use Boltzmann pick). verification_result_cid is None (no Lean verification on the seed; id=24 only halts on missing telemetry CAS bytes, NOT on missing VerificationResult). Predecessor TB-16.x.2.5 r2 hash c19dfcbe (which broke audit id=24) superseded.  # rehashed by TB-16.x.2.5 (2026-05-05; architect umbrella charter §2 Atom 2.5 — AutopsyCapsule real-bankruptcy chain): ADDITIVE arena driver hook. TURINGOS_FORCE_BANKRUPTCY_AFTER_ACCEPTED=<staker>:<stake_micro> env-var: AFTER preseed (TaskOpen + EscrowLock + optional CompleteSetSeed) but BEFORE the LLM swarm starts, injects a real-signed WorkTx via make_real_worktx_signed_by(predicate_passes=true) so stakes_t has ≥1 entry for `task-{run_id}` at the time TURINGOS_FORCE_BANKRUPTCY=1 emits TaskBankruptcyTx (line ~3150). The TB-15 dispatch arm Step 3.5 hook (sequencer.rs:1374) then calls derive_autopsies_for_bankruptcy(pre_econ, bk, ...) which iterates stakes_t and emits an AgentAutopsyCapsule with loss_reason_class=Bankruptcy + loss_amount = stake.amount. Closes the missing R2 P4 path "WorkTx-accepted → got accepted → then the task went bankrupt". The seeded WorkTx is REAL (real Ed25519 signature via AgentKeypairRegistry, real predicate_results, real stake debit from preseeded balance) — NOT a synthetic-rejection gate (compare make_synthetic_worktx at line ~1086 which uses synthetic_rejection_for_l4e_gate=true → L4.E only). Pairs with TURINGOS_FORCE_BANKRUPTCY=1 to materialize WorkTx (admit) → TerminalSummary → TaskBankruptcy → AutopsyCapsule in CAS + AutopsyIndex entry in agent_autopsies_t. Predecessor TB-16.x.2.3 hash e1c4d057 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-16.x.2.3 (2026-05-05; architect umbrella charter §2 Atom 2.3 — CompleteSetRedeem env-var trigger): ADDITIVE arena driver hook. TURINGOS_FORCE_REDEEM=<owner>:<outcome>:<share_units> env-var: BEFORE bundle.shutdown (parallel to FORCE_CHALLENGE_RESOLVE; OUTSIDE the MaxTxExhausted EvidenceCapsule conditional so it fires on both OMEGA-Confirm success and MaxTxExhausted+FORCE_BANKRUPTCY paths), constructs an agent-signed CompleteSetRedeemTx via make_real_complete_set_redeem_signed_by + submits via bus.submit_typed_tx. Pairs with TURINGOS_COMPLETE_SET_SEED (mints provider's YES+NO shares) + TURINGOS_FORCE_BANKRUPTCY (transitions market to Bankrupt → NO wins) to produce a single chain containing CompleteSetMint → TaskBankruptcy → CompleteSetRedeem sequence — closes the missing 6th system-emitted tx kind in the R3 Round 2 chain (raises 11-of-13 → 12-of-13). DEVIATION-FROM-CHARTER per feedback_architect_deviation_stance: charter §2 Atom 2.3 spec'd 4 env-var parts (owner:event_id:outcome:share); implementation uses 3 (owner:outcome:share_units) — event_id auto-derived from `task-{run_id}` because run_id contains a unix-ms timestamp minted at evaluator entry (run_id.rs:21) and is unpredictable from the smoke script. Mirrors FORCE_BANKRUPTCY's auto-deri