ash eb718a23 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-16.x.2.1 (2026-05-04; architect umbrella charter §2 Atom 2.1 — TaskExpire env-var trigger): ADDITIVE arena driver hook. TURINGOS_FORCE_EXPIRE=1 env-var: after MaxTxExhausted EvidenceCapsule write + (optional) FORCE_BANKRUPTCY emit, calls tb11_emit_expire_for_eligible(seq, current_logical_t=next_logical_t_peek(), expiry_delta_logical_t=0) so every Open/Bankrupt task with elapsed > 0 emits a TaskExpireTx (ExpireReason::Deadline for Open; ExpireReason::BankruptcyTriggered when FORCE_BANKRUPTCY also fired). Mirrors FORCE_BANKRUPTCY's tb8_await_state_root_advance(pre_ex_root, 5000) prelude so prior commits land before the q_snapshot read. Closes the missing 4th system-emitted tx kind in R3 Round 2 chain (raises 9-of-13 → 10-of-13). Predecessor TB-16 Atom 7 R1 Step 3 hash 729a4c5e superseded.  # rehashed by TB-16 Atom 7 R1 Step 3 (2026-05-04; architect §7.3 FR-16.3 + FR-16.4 + FR-16.7): ADDITIVE arena driver hooks. (1) TURINGOS_FORCE_CHALLENGER=<agent_id> env-var: after VerifyTx OMEGA-Confirm and before FinalizeReward emit, the named agent submits a real-signed ChallengeTx targeting the WorkTx (FR-16.3). (2) TURINGOS_COMPLETE_SET_SEED=<provider>:<amount_micro> env-var: after preseed EscrowLock, the named provider submits MarketSeedTx + CompleteSetMintTx against the task's EventId (FR-16.4). (3) TURINGOS_FORCE_BANKRUPTCY=1 env-var: after MAX_TX exhaustion + TerminalSummary emit, sequencer.emit_system_tx(TaskBankruptcy{...}) fires referencing the same EvidenceCapsule (FR-16.7 → autopsy emission via TB-15 dispatch arm Step 3.5). All three are env-var-gated; no behavior change to existing user-task / preseed paths. Predecessor TB-14 Atom 6 follow-up hash 3530a2d5 superseded.  # rehashed by TB-14 Atom 6 follow-up (2026-05-03; architect ruling step 1 — Codex R1 primary VETO closure): the canonical TxId returned by `boltzmann_select_parent_v2` MUST NOT flow into legacy shadow `bus.append` parent_id (kernel.tape uses a different (shadow)